Reference Object.content:
A simple object to allow referencing other components in the specification, internally and externally.The Reference Object is defined by JSON Reference and follows the same structure, behavior and rules. A JSON Reference SHALL only be used to refer to a schema that is formatted in either JSON or YAML. In the case of a YAML-formatted Schema, the JSON Reference SHALL be applied to the JSON representation of that schema. The JSON representation SHALL be made by applying the conversion described here.For this specification, reference resolution is done as defined by the JSON Reference specification and not by the JSON Schema specification.Fixed FieldsField NameTypeDescription$refstringREQUIRED. The reference string.This object cannot be extended with additional properties and any properties added SHALL be ignored.Reference Object Example1{
2  "$ref": "#/components/schemas/Pet"
3}  $ref: '#/components/schemas/Pet'

